editGasEducationHighExplanation.message: This is best for time sensitive transactions (like Swaps) as it increases the likelihood of a successful transaction. If a Swap takes too long to process it may fail and result in losing some of your gas fee.

editGasEducationLowExplanation.message: A lower gas fee should only be used when processing time is less important. Lower fees make it hard predict when (or if) your transaction will be successful.

editGasEducationMediumExplanation.message: A medium gas fee is good for sending, withdrawing or other non-time sensitive transactions. This setting will most often result in a successful transaction.
